Thank you for all of your hard work and dedication this year, HORNET PRIDE !

post_text: The mission of the Early College High School at Delaware State University centers on the learning of ALL students. We firmly believe that our young people are being prepared to change the world. Now, in this time of turmoil in our country, we must come together to give ALL young people a fighting chance regardless of their race, creed, or color. We must continue to educate them to be leaders. ECHS Families, we pray that your families are safe from harm from violence, racism, and the pandemic. Remember that our staff is here for you should you need us. We are all in this together.

post_text: Congratulations to the Early College HS @ DSU Business Professionals of America Chapter for their hard work and dedication this school year. Yesterday, Wednesday, May 20th, 2020 at 7pm via LIVE on YouTube, the ECHS chapter was awarded the Quality Chapter Distinction Award. This award is given to chapters who abide by the National Center guidelines towards WSAP Competitive Events, BPA Cares and Membership. Our Chapter President Jalen Johnston was awarded the GOLD USA Presidential Volunteer Service Award!!!! Way to go, Jalen. There would not be an ECHS BPA chapter if you did not advocate for it when you were a freshmen! We are proud of you.

post_text: Normally when it's Teacher Appreciation Week, the ECHS Administration puts little gifts in all of the teachers' mailboxes to show them how much we all care about them. This year, we had to be clever, as we only have the teachers' "Inboxes." Day #1 was yesterday, so we gave them the gift of inspiration: a newsletter filled with inspirational messages. Today, on Day#2, we gave them the gift of laughter, a newsletter filled with funny videos and memes to make them belly laugh! More to come as the week moves on!

Student Leaders Week Spotlight

Hornets in Action President: Mahogany George

Mahogany oversees all of the projects and events for Hornets In Action. She has taken the lead and initiated the Manna Bags project where she collected, counted, and organized all the donations, lead contact for the candy gram sales, participated in Students in Actions hosted by ECHS, held recruitment meetings for freshmen interest and participation, and maintained club documents. She also would lead the HIA meetings after school!

Thanks for your leadership, Mahogany! #HornetPride #Catchit #NSLW2020

ECHS Technology Reminder for Students:

1. If it is a connectivity problem, you will need to contact your internet provider to discuss.

2. If it is a problem getting into Schoology (Forgot my logon info) Contact Dr. Edney or Mrs. McCants to look up your info and send it to you.

3. If you cannot remember your Home Access Center (HAC) login to see report cards or interim reports, please contact Mrs. McCants.

4. If your computer or charger is not working, please click on the Technology Link below and fill out the form to let our Tech Guy, Mr. Zach know what the issue is. He will contact you to see how we need to handle the issue.

Dr. Edney

post_text: Before jumping into two-column geometric proofs, students learn through a hands-on activity: creating origami structures. The paper is the "given, " the folding steps are the "proof, " and the final origami structure is the "conclusion/prove." Students will be able to transfer this learning to mathematical principles with a clear understanding.

post_text: Way to go to our very own LaKiera!!! She has been nominated to be a member of the Delaware State University Board of Trustees Chair’s Student Circle (CSC) because of her leadership abilities and interest in learning more about the Board of Trustees and university governance. The CSC has been established to provide an opportunity for open dialogue between the Board of Trustees and students to better understand student needs, issues and life experiences as well as to increase understanding by students of the role of the Board. Additionally, this forum will provide an opportunity for informal mentoring between trustees and members of the CSC. Way to go, Lakeria! We are proud of you and know that you will represent the students of ECHS well!

post_text: ECHS had a busy day yesterday. Our freshmen took the PSAT 8/9 test. The sophomores took the DeSSA Science test. The juniors took the DeSSA Social Studies rest. And after a long morning of testing, the seniors kicked off their last pep rally with a parade in their honor. They sported pennants with the names of the colleges they plan to attend next year. The band, chorus, and dancer rocked the house. And we even had some fun and games! Great job, Mrs. Dara Laws Savage for leading this.

shared_text:
Teensharp
March 20, 2019 at 5:18 PM ·

Quick shout-out to four amazing College Access Ambassador scholars from TeenSHARP Delaware on their amazing achievement earlier this month!

Elijah, a junior from Tatnall, Nia a junior from Sanford, Kayla, a junior from MOT Charter High School, and Daniel, a junior from Early College High School, were selected to present on educational inequity at Rutgers-Camden!

So proud of our CAAT scholars! I’m telling you - they WILL change the world! ❤️👏🏻

➡️ ❗️Do you know a scholar with immense potential? We are currently accepting applications for our next cohort of scholars! Applications will close May 30 for CAAT.

📅 APPLY TODAY: Www.tinyurl.com/TeenSHARP2019

Representing: MOT Charter School, The Tatnall School, Sanford School, & Early College High School at Delaware State University

shared_text:
Delaware BPA
March 9, 2019 at 1:32 PM ·

#DelawareBPA is proud to spotlight Rico Johnson (@hoodie.rico_)for his terrific and outstanding contributions to Business Professionals of America at the Local, State and National Level .Rico currently attend the Early College High School @ Delaware State University where he serves as the Chapter President. Rico is always there in the time of need helping out without a doubt. When ever you need motivation or something to brighten up your day Rico will do what ever it takes to make you laugh.I know that BPA will be left in the hands of Business Professionals taking on the world. Thanks for everything you do Rico!!!! #BPAAllDay #TogetherWeCreateEarly College High School at Delaware State University Hannah KimJalen JohnstonParth Patel
